On Friday, August 13, 2004, at 02:18PM, Michael Knight <vwdormer(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>Anybody have these posts saved or know how to do a Leak Down Test on the TIV 
>engines. Any help will be appreciated.

You need to buy a tester (get the kind with two gauges) and you need a supply of compressed air. Bring each cylinder to TDC to do the measurement. You want to measure the percentage of leak down as well as the maximum difference between any two cylinders.

